Commentary: the Sufi doctrine that the Quran is contained in the Fâlihah
  (the opening chapter), which itself is contained in the Bismillâh (’In the
  Name of God"; the opening words), which is contained in the letter ba,
  which is contained in its diacritical point.
---
From that point depend heaven and all nature.
